channel.title: Beat the Clock #18: 5 Minutes of Auxy
channel.description:
Time to beat the clock! This time in a more literal sense than usual.
### The challenge: Show what you can do in 5 minutes?
Here's how:
- [Turn on](https://www.cnet.com/how-to/how-to-use-ios-11-built-in-screen-recording-feature/) screen recording in OS 11 - Set a timer for 5 minutes - Open Auxy and create a new project - Make music until the timer ends - Make sure to hit play so we can hear what you ended up with before stopping the screen recording - Upload your screen recording to YouTube and post a link in this thread
Here's an example by @s0phont: https://youtu.be/gQ7ZtQ7tzQA
Keep in mind that this challenge is really about having fun and seeing how people use the app, so don't try to impress by preparing and making several attempts. Just record once and submit.
On Monday we'll check the entries to see how things turn out.
Go!

item.title: Beat the Clock #18: 5 Minutes of Auxy
item.dc:creator: Auxy
item.description:
I’ve watched all the entries now and it’s really valuable for us to get a glimpse into how you guys use the app. I also think it’s inspiring for people to see how other people use the app. Hoping that you can learn from watching each other.

The question is how we can get more people to post more videos showing their best tips and tricks on a regular basis? Would love to hear all your thoughts on that.

Thanks for all the nice videos! On Friday we’ll be back with a “normal” BTC. Stay tuned…
